 serious students of the New Testament.A detailed introduction examines the provenance, codex and paleography of P. Bodmer III, presents the singular readings discovered in the text, and separates these readings into meaningful categories. Finally, the appendices provide a complete list of the 1,960 singular readings, a brief description of the 119 corrections made by the original scribe, and a quick reference to the location of all corrections to Kasser's 1958 transcription, as well as corrections to citations in the NA 28th edition.This work will prove a valuable asset to anyone interested in Coptic Biblical studies, New Testament textual criticism, scribal habits, and other related fields.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Coptic.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aBiblexManuscripts (Papyri)xCriticism, Textual. 4aBodmer. 4aGenesis. 4aJohannesevangelium. 4akoptisch. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / New Testament.2bisacsh  aBodmer.  aCoptic.  aGenesis.  aJohn.1 aSharp, Daniel B., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2017 Part 1z978311076249508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theology, Relig. Studies, Jewish Studies 2016z9783110485394oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831104363030 cprintz978311044193240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311044422340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110444223423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110444223/original  a978-3-11-071954-3  DG Plus eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-076249-5  DG Plus DeG Package 2017 Part 1b2017  aEBA_BACK